The paper discusses aggregation issues for composite solutions, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of various solution structures such as sets, set morphologies, and trees suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.PL). The consideration of resource constraints and profit also indicates a systems engineering (cs.SY) perspective. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
